===Pronunciation===

:Mi'krO kline

===Etymology===

:From the Greek mikron - "little" and klinein - "to stoop."

===Noun===
#A common [[feldspar]] of [[igneous]], [[plutonic]], and [[metamorphic]] [[rock]]s. Microcline is the main feldspar of [[granite]] and is present in almost every [[pegmatite]] occurrence. The bluish-green variety is called [[Amazonstone]], and is sometimes of gem quality. Used in [[ceramics]], ceramic [[glaze]]s, and as a scouring powder.

=== Chemical composition ===
*Potassium aluminum silicate, <math>KAlSi_3O_8</math>
 
=== Physical properties ===

*Moh's Hardness: 6.0
*Specific gravity: 2.5-2.6
*Color: white, flesh, yellow, red-brown, green
*Luster: glassy
*Fracture: conchoidal
*Cleavage: two good, nearly at right angles.
*Habit: Triclinic - pinacoidal. [[Crystal]]s may be several feet across, in contrast to the much smaller [[orthoclase]] crystals.

